			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hi all!<BR>
<BR>
This spell is VERY great.  Keep it at rdy at all the time.  But hopefully you never use it.  It is a emergency spell!  You can make a quick mes on all mob and don`t hesistate to do it if the battle is going very nasty (or while you wait for single mes (like Dazzle) to be accesible for recast.  Even if it mes you, it can be a VERY good spell to use, since it go off on you faster then on mob and can keep mesing all monsters around non-stop with no real trouble (1 attack or 2 maybe before finishing recast).  The trouble with this spell is the slow duration and low reliability.  In other words, it is the emergency solution and you pray.  Single mes is way more long duration, you can separate the mob as you wish in single, not with this spell.  Hint, if you recast it, re-mes all but one(he resist), this is a very good time to single mes the one that resist (be sure the AE is off on target).<BR>
<BR>
This spell is a life saver for all and if you hear : ZONE!!!  Cast it on the central mob (or whatever seem central mob), you may allow all the group to zone...or to change mind and clear room (usually the main healer mana status should be first account for a staying...and yours:))<BR>
<BR>
But a group that ask for this spell as a first solution is a group that don`t understand the spell, you cannot do much other stuff while keeping this spell up at all the time, after single mes are all done, you can be at rdy for whatever!  And if you mes yourself with it, don`t cry, if you mes 2 or more monsters with you, you are doing a good job for group (oky, it will be better not messing you, but sometimes life is hard) and cleric should do all he can to keep you alive and re-mesing the 2+ dumb mob...:)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
